    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "sigmoid_2016_retarget",
    "description": "Tests Proposal 2 (Biais et al. 2019 sigmoid) in the 2016-block retarget regime.\nSweep10b (baseline oracle) showed all 5 econ levels going v27_dominant via the retarget cascade. The sigmoid oracle created 2.7x higher pool opportunity costs in the 144-block test (sweep_0001: $2.49M vs $922K baseline). The question is whether this amplified pricing changes cascade timing or flips outcomes in the 2016-block regime where the retarget cascade is the dominant mechanism.\nResearch question: Does sigmoid change the minimum economic_split needed for v27 to win via the 2016-block retarget cascade? Specifically, does econ=0.50 or 0.35 flip outcomes that were v27_dominant in sweep10b?\nRun across FOUR namespaces for faster completion (split scenarios across pairs):\n\n  Sweep A \u2014 baseline, scenarios 0-2 (econ=0.35, 0.50, 0.60):\n    python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n      --input sigmoid_2016_retarget/build_manifest.json \\\n      --namespace sweep-2016-base-a \\\n      --results-dir sigmoid_2016_retarget/results_baseline \\\n      --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n      --scenarios sweep_0000 sweep_0001 sweep_0002\n\n  Sweep B \u2014 baseline, scenarios 3-4 (econ=0.70, 0.82):\n    python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n      --input sigmoid_2016_retarget/build_manifest.json \\\n      --namespace sweep-2016-base-b \\\n      --results-dir sigmoid_2016_retarget/results_baseline \\\n      --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n      --scenarios sweep_0003 sweep_0004\n\n  Sweep C \u2014 sigmoid, scenarios 0-2 (econ=0.35, 0.50, 0.60):\n    python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n      --input sigmoid_2016_retarget/build_manifest.json \\\n      --namespace sweep-2016-sig-a \\\n      --results-dir sigmoid_2016_retarget/results_sigmoid \\\n      --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n      --use-sigmoid \\\n      --scenarios sweep_0000 sweep_0001 sweep_0002\n\n  Sweep D \u2014 sigmoid, scenarios 3-4 (econ=0.70, 0.82):\n    python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n      --input sigmoid_2016_retarget/build_manifest.json \\\n      --namespace sweep-2016-sig-b \\\n      --results-dir sigmoid_2016_retarget/results_sigmoid \\\n      --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n      --use-sigmoid \\\n      --scenarios sweep_0003 sweep_0004\n\nNamespaces to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-2016-base-a\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-2016-base-b\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-2016-sig-a\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-2016-sig-b\n\nWall-clock estimate with 4 parallel namespaces:\n  A+C run simultaneously: 3 scenarios x 13,000s = ~11h\n  B+D run simultaneously: 2 scenarios x 13,000s = ~7.5h\n  Overall bottleneck: ~11h (done by morning)\n\nNOTE: Sweeps A+B share results_baseline dir; C+D share results_sigmoid dir. The sweep runner handles concurrent writes safely (different scenario subdirs).\n",
